Auto Inferno is a one stop portal for license installation and many more. This portal helps user to install new licenses into the production server with fast and seamless way. 

Usability of the portal:
1. Install new licenses:
Step1: Visit the Auto Inferno dashboard autoinferno.com
step2: Select vendor, server, operation, upload new license files (txt format) and write any valuable comments.
step3: Click submit button to submit the current request and initiate the process or click reset button to reset all the selected fields.
step4: On Submit based on the options selected above the exiting file is modified and a new updated file is generated:
How updated license file is generated:
-First three lines SERVER/USE_SERVER/DAEMON/VENDOR remain as they currently exist
-If Merge request then keep the existing FEATURES as it is and append new FEATURES into the -license file.
-If Replace request then remove all contents below the DAEMON line and copy FEATURES of new  license file.
step5: Once updated license file is generated, the portal compares the FEATURES difference between the exisitng file and the updated file and shows the comparison details in the dashboard.
step6: After verification, if they are not satisfied with the comparison details then they can click on ABORT button that will logs and abort the current request.
step7: If user is satisfied with the comparison details then they can click on submit button that will push the updated file to the production server.

2. Change Logs:
step1: Visit the Auto Inferno change log page autoinferno/change-log
step2: Each request or action is logged to make it easy to track changes. Each log provides details such as 
-Vendor : Vendor name
-Server : Server name
-DateTime started : Time request was submitted
-DateTime completed : Time request was completed
-Files : Provide option to view and download existing, new, updated and comparison files with feature to visualize side by side comparison of the existing file and updated file.


3. Check Features Expiry:
step1: Visit the Auto Inferno Expiry page autoinferno/expiry
step2: Feature Expiry is classified into two categories:
 - Critical: Critical features are those that are getting expired within coming 15 days and do      not have any redundant license file with those features.
 - Non-Critical: These are the features that are fetched based on the user input selection like    expiry interval, Vendor and Server.

4. Master List:
step1: Visit the Auto Inferno Master List page autoinferno/master-list
step2: Admins can add, update or delete records 

5. License Access:
step1: Visit the Auto Inferno License Access page autoinferno/license-access
step2: User can enter AID, select Vendor and Server to gain access to a license.

6. Charts:
step1: Visit the Auto Inferno Charts page autoinferno/charts
step2: User can first see the number of regions, server and vendor available. 
step3: User can also see the pie chart visualization of server count by regions and vendor count or specific vendor count by regions
step4: User can also see the bar chart comparison visualization of portion occupied by vendors in different regions.
